        <mxCell id="n171" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FDF2E3;strokeColor=#D86613;fontColor=#D86613;fontSize=9;fontStyle=1;arcSize=8;dashed=0;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacing=4;" value="&lt; 12 HOURS EXCELLENT ✓ Near-optimal recovery performance" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="76" width="250" x="1256" y="1396" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n172" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#CBD3D9;fontColor=#232F3E;fontSize=9;fontStyle=0;arcSize=8;dashed=0;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=4;" value="KEY NOTES • All inter-VPC traffic between Core and Protected Data is inspected by AWS Network Firewall. • No direct routing exists from Recovery Access VPC to Protected Data VPC. • Backup ingestion connectivity is enabled only during approved windows. • All repositories and backups use S3 Object Lock (immutable) and encryption. • All logs are delivered to a centralized logging account with tamper protection." vertex="1">
